<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB08296</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT ENHANCING THE CONTINUING PROFESSIONAL DEVELOPMENT OF FILIPINO WORKERS AND PROFESSIONALS, AMENDING FOR THE PURPOSE REPUBLIC ACT NO. 10912, OTHERWISE KNOWN AS THE "CONTINUING PROFESSIONAL DEVELOPMENT ACT OF 2016"</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Seeks to amend some provisions of Republic Act No.10912 with the following provisions:

a) That registered and licensed professional are exempted from compliance within the FIRST FIVE YEARS after obtaining their licenses;

b) That failure to comply with CPD shall only be a basis to deny renewal of Professional Identification Cards after the lapse of the compliance period; 

c) That licensed Professional OFWs shall be exempted from the requirement for the period of their overseas employment; and

d) That professionals shall only be required to obtain a maximum of 36 CPD credit units once every five years.

</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>RODRIGUEZ, MAXIMO JR.B.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2018-09-26</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Nieto (000 2018-11-29)</td><td>2. Del Mar (000 2019-01-29)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>COMMITEE HEARINGS/ACTIONS:</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp1. Under study by the Technical Working Group(TWG) on 2018-11-12</b><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON HIGHER AND TECHNICAL EDUCATION ON 2018-10-01</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SECONDARILY REFERRED TO THE COMMITTEE(S) ON CIVIL SERVICE AND PROFESSIONAL REGULATION</td></tr></table>